able to get a dress

00:28.962 --> 00:31.463
<i>where my mom is not gonna
approve of it.</i>

00:31.498 --> 00:32.831
So I'm a little bit worried
about that.

00:32.866 --> 00:35.167
[Candace] There has to be
something here.

00:35.201 --> 00:36.568
This is a no.

00:36.603 --> 00:38.237
These last-minute brides

00:38.271 --> 00:39.571
send me on a whirlwind.

00:39.606 --> 00:40.939
- Mom's making a face.
- Mom?

00:40.973 --> 00:43.742
I have a little bit
of a reservation right here.

00:43.777 --> 00:45.778
- [Shaela] Of what?
- [Lisa] About this?

00:45.812 --> 00:48.180
- We'll deal with your mother.
- Okay.

00:48.214 --> 00:49.181
[Shameika] Oh.

00:50.583 --> 00:52.551
Hey, I like that one
way better than the first one.

00:52.585 --> 00:55.220
Now the first one
is a definite no?

00:55.255 --> 00:56.455
Yeah. I'm telling you now.

00:56.489 --> 00:58.490
I didn't like it,
but I like this one.

00:58.525 --> 01:01.193
You should have been honest
when I first came out.

01:01.227 --> 01:02.361
<i>It's down to the wire.</i>

01:02.395 --> 01:05.164
I am feeling like what the hell.

01:09.602 --> 01:12.304
[upbeat music playing]

01:15.575 --> 01:18.944
Okay. Let me call Randy.

01:22.782 --> 01:25.684
Is that Chewie? Oh, yeah.
Chill, boo-boo.

01:25.718 --> 01:28.320
Come here, you wanna play
with daddy?

01:28.354 --> 01:30.122
- [Dorothy] Randy?
- Oh.

01:32.225 --> 01:34.893
<i>Oh, Dorothy, I'm here.</i>

01:34.928 --> 01:35.828
- How you doing?
- [Dorothy] Listen,

01:35.862 --> 01:37.629
we got the new dresses
and I wanna show you

01:37.664 --> 01:40.432
- and go over some of them.
- Yay.

01:40.467 --> 01:42.501
<i>I know I'm still working
with brides every day</i>

01:42.535 --> 01:44.536
