01:53.780 --> 01:56.281
- [Dorothy]<i> Okay.</i>
- [Randy]<i> ...I'm coming back.</i>

01:56.316 --> 01:57.449
[Dorothy]<i> Great.</i>

01:57.484 --> 02:00.652
So, the first one we got
and I absolutely adore.

02:00.687 --> 02:02.988
- That's Bentley. Very simple.
- [Dorothy]<i> It's beautiful.</i>

02:03.022 --> 02:05.324
[Randy]<i> That dress is doing</i>
<i>really, really well</i>

02:05.358 --> 02:06.492
<i>in Europe, by the way.</i>

02:06.526 --> 02:08.293
[Dorothy] It's elegant
and timeless.

02:08.328 --> 02:10.229
This one I'm obsessed with.

02:10.263 --> 02:11.730
I love the slit.

02:11.764 --> 02:13.465
I love everything
about this dress.

02:13.500 --> 02:18.303
Isn't the back, like,
absolutely sexy, sexy, sexy?

02:18.338 --> 02:20.038
And then we have Betsy.

02:20.073 --> 02:21.373
[Randy]<i> Betsy is a</i> great dress
because I think

02:21.407 --> 02:23.775
<i>it looks really great
on a curvy girl.</i>

02:23.810 --> 02:25.577
<i>Oh, there goes Chewie.
He hears the guys downstairs.</i>

02:25.612 --> 02:27.446
- [Dorothy] Chewie?
- [Randy]<i> Yeah.</i>

02:27.480 --> 02:28.580
<i>He hears my workers
working on the house.</i>

02:28.615 --> 02:30.516
<i>He's watching out for me.</i>

02:30.550 --> 02:32.417
<i>Good boy.</i>

02:32.452 --> 02:34.686
I love you and send all
the girls and the consultants

02:34.721 --> 02:37.189
and Mara and Ronnie my love,
okay?

02:37.223 --> 02:38.323
I certainly will. Mwah.

02:38.358 --> 02:41.527
- Okay. Mwah, bye-bye.
- Bye. Bye.

02:41.561 --> 02:43.195
[upbeat music playing]

02:44.831 --> 02:47.399
We are heading
to the airport in Atlanta.

02:47.433 --> 02:50.402
My fiance is about
to drop me off.

02:50.436 --> 02:52.838
- Yes.
- Okay, now, be careful.

02:52.872 --> 02:55.741
<i>Dalen, my fiance,
is a TV personality.</i>

02:55.775 --> 02:59.378
He hunts ghosts for a living
on the hit show,

02:59.412 --> 03:01.747
The Ghost Brothers.

03:01.781 --> 03:04.783
<i>Dalen proposed right before
New Year's,</i>

03:04.817 --> 03:07.653
